@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About us";
}
<h2>About Us</h2>
<style>
    .about-container {
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 20px;
        background-color: #f9f9f9;
        border: 1px solid #ddd;
        border-radius: 8px;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
    }

    .about h2 {
        color: #333;
        font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    .about p {
        color: #555;
        font-family: 'Georgia', serif;
        line-height: 1.6;
        margin-bottom: 15px;
    }

    .about p strong {
        color: #222;
    }


        .about h2 {
            font-size: 24px;
        }

        .about p {
            font-size: 16px;
        }
    }
</style>

<div class="about-container">
    <p class="about">
        <strong>A Canadian family company</strong><br>
        The story of Orion began in 1991 – on this date Alexandra and Alex Thomas  founded the Orion company. In 2014 their son Alexander joined the family company to lead it successfully into the future.
    </p>
    <p class="about">
        Today Orion is a leading Canadian manufacturer of writing utensils and accessories for school and business. More than 80 employees are based in Windsor – the unique pens are available in about 56 countries around the world.
    </p>
    <p class="about">
        <strong>Made in Canada – Our company location in Windsor</strong><br>
        At Orion we value consistently high and sustainable quality. That´s why we produce mainly in Canada.
    </p>
    <p class="about">
        <strong>Pens distinguished by innovation, functionality and design</strong><br>
        Orion takes you into the fascinating world of writing. With enthusiasm and passion we develop high quality products which are distinguished by innovation, functionality and design. The huge choice of different designs and writing systems or nib widths and the creative products like handlettering and calligraphy offer the right writing experience for everyone.
    </p>
    <p class="about">
        <strong>How Orion got its name</strong><br>
        In 1991, amidst Canada's flourishing penmanship, we sought a name that blended modernity with the art of writing. "Orion" emerged—a symbol of celestial elegance and timeless craftsmanship. It signified our commitment to pioneering quality and innovation in the world of pens, where every stroke tells a story of creativity and precision.“.
    </p>
</div>
